The Nigeria Army on Monday said it has neutralised a girl with person-borne explosives device at a check point in Adamawa. This was disclosed via a tweet by the Nigerian Army official handle. The tweet reads “Troops of 143 Battalion deployed at a check point in Gulak Adamawa State, neutralised a girl with Person-Borne Improvised Explosive Device who tried to Infiltrate DAR Village to detonate her explosive vest in the early hours of 26 November 2018.” It added; “The gallant troops in conjunction with hunters and vigilantes immediately cordoned off the incident area and subsequently conducted perimeter patrol around the community to ensure the area is cleared and to also exploit the area for BHT activities. Pictures are shown below.” Details later…  Photo credit: @HQNigerianArmy